"""Rewrite all 12 bot sysprompts to best-practice structure (2026-06-09).

Research (Anthropic/OpenAI/LlamaIndex + arXiv 2024-25): a good RAG system prompt =
identity → grounding+allow-compute → quote-before-answer → 3-tier refusal →
citation, kept at ~800-2000 tokens. Audit found 2 bots BLOATED (test-spa 8082 tok,
thong-tu 4945 tok → over the ~3000-tok degradation threshold, refuse-heavy,
internally contradictory → over-refusal + lost-in-the-middle). The other 10 were
already sweet-spot but lacked the explicit allow-compute + 3-tier-refusal core.

This rewrites ALL 12 onto one universal CORE (per-bot only customizes identity /
refusal / citation). test-spa keeps its booking-action guide ({captured_slots});
y-te keeps the medical disclaimer. New sizes: every bot now 727-1087 tokens.

Old prompts embedded in downgrade (fully reversible); also human-readable backup
at docs/bots/sysprompt_backup_20260609.md. Generator: scripts/build_sysprompts_20260609.py.
Rule 7 (alembic), no-psql. A/B-gated (load test must hold HALLU=0 + Coverage).
"""
